    "content": "<p>The figure shows a propped cantilever with uniform flexural rigidity EI (in N.m²) and subjected to a moment $M$ (in N.m). Consider forces and displacements in the upward direction as positive.</p>\n<p>Find the upward reaction at the propped support B (in N) when this support settles by $(-\\Delta)$, given in metres.</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbjbp5mx/177b6c06-31c4-42ce-bcde-bdeca905a618/6d1bdb90-4204-11f0-83ec-3540d3e31406/file-jaoe38c1mbjbp5my.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbjbp5mx/177b6c06-31c4-42ce-bcde-bdeca905a618/6d1bdb90-4204-11f0-83ec-3540d3e31406/file-jaoe38c1mbjbp5my.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2025 Set 2 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Propped Cantilever Beam Question 1 English\">",
