    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>$$ \\text { Reaction due to moment, } $$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbjbqbx0/59e8216a-872c-4982-a97f-ddf4c05a0a7c/8dc4e940-4204-11f0-83ec-3540d3e31406/file-jaoe38c1mbjbqbx1.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbjbqbx0/59e8216a-872c-4982-a97f-ddf4c05a0a7c/8dc4e940-4204-11f0-83ec-3540d3e31406/file-jaoe38c1mbjbqbx1.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2025 Set 2 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Propped Cantilever Beam Question 1 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>Deflection at $B=0$</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} \\frac{M L^2}{2 E I}-\\frac{R_m L^3}{3 E I} &amp; =0 \\\\ R_m &amp; =\\frac{3}{2}\\left(\\frac{M}{L}\\right) \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Reaction at propped end due to sinking of support.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbjbr3ul/caa99fa4-347c-47d9-8562-e14df31ffa99/a358bed0-4204-11f0-83ec-3540d3e31406/file-jaoe38c1mbjbr3um.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbjbr3ul/caa99fa4-347c-47d9-8562-e14df31ffa99/a358bed0-4204-11f0-83ec-3540d3e31406/file-jaoe38c1mbjbr3um.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2025 Set 2 Strength of Materials Or Solid Mechanics - Propped Cantilever Beam Question 1 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>$$ \\text { Net reaction at propped end is } $$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbjbshao/d0ca69d6-8edf-4444-accd-d1256fbc841b/c98b0900-4204-11f0-83ec-3540d3e31406/file-jaoe38c1mbjbshap.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbjbshao/d0ca69d6-8edf-4444-accd-d1256fbc841b/c98b0900-4204-11f0-83ec-3540d3e31406/file-jaoe38c1mbjbshap.png\" load